definition.name: Film

fields.name: description
fields.description: A short description or plot summary of the film.

fields.name: filmId
fields.description: A surrogate primary key used to uniquely identify each film in the table.

fields.name: languageId
fields.description: A foreign key pointing at the language table; identifies the language of the film.

fields.name: lastUpdate
fields.description: When the row was created or most recently updated.

fields.name: length
fields.description: The duration of the film, in minutes.

fields.name: originalLanguageId
fields.description: A foreign key pointing at the language table; identifies the original language of the film. Used when a film has been dubbed into a new language.

fields.name: rating
fields.description: The rating assigned to the film. Can be one of: G, PG, PG-13, R, or NC-17.

fields.name: releaseYear
fields.description: The year in which the movie was released.

fields.name: rentalDuration
fields.description: The length of the rental period, in days.

fields.name: rentalRate
fields.description: The cost to rent the film for the period specified in the rental_duration column.

fields.name: replacementCost
fields.description: The amount charged to the customer if the film is not returned or is returned in a damaged state.

fields.name: specialFeatures
fields.description: Lists which common special features are included on the DVD. Can be zero or more of: Trailers, Commentaries, Deleted Scenes, Behind the Scenes.

fields.name: title
fields.description: The title of the film.
